<!--
VOICING PLAN:
The Comforter Has Come is in C major (no accidentals). The melody sits in octave 4-5 range.

Phrase structure: verse (mm. 1-8) × 2 + refrain (mm. 13-21).

Phrase 1 (mm. 1-4): Light two-voice RH (2 notes), 3-4 voice LH. I "334" in LH gives the open
  C3-E3-G3-C4 bass voicing. IV "43" for brief IV chords at cadence points.

Phrase 2 (mm. 5-8): Quartal "44" color (G4-C5) for I chord in RH. vi in m7 uses "333" for
  Am7 richness, providing color before V half-cadence.

Verse 2 (mm. 9-12): 7th chords throughout. IΔ, IVΔ in both hands. ii7 "333" in m11.

Refrain (mm. 13-21): Climax. E5 melody notes with I "334" 4-note RH chords.
  m14 has I→V7 in one measure — V7 "333" G2-B2-D3-F3 in LH is the clearest dominant sound.
  m16 ii-I alternation creates rhythmic tension.
  m20: I→V7→I for pre-final cadence.
  m21: C1 pedal bass + full I root position landing.

TEXTURE ARC:
mm. 0-4: Light pickup (2-note RH), grows to 4-voice LH with "334" patterns.
mm. 5-8: Quartal color, more voice activity (arpeggio in m2).
mm. 9-12: 7th chords, fuller LH (IVΔ with E4 in m4, m11).
mm. 13-21: Full refrain, 4-note RH chords, C1 pedal reinforcement in final measure.
-->
